properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued January 4 at 3:22AM MST until January 5 at 2:00AM MST by NWS Billings MT
properties.description:
* WHAT...Westerly winds with gusts 50 to 60 mph expected.

* WHERE...Red Lodge Foothills and Southeastern Carbon.

* WHEN...From 11 AM today to 2 AM MST Sunday. Strongest winds late
today and early this evening.

* IMPACTS...Blown down trees or fences possible. Travel could be
difficult, especially for high profile vehicles.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Due to unseasonably mild and dry
conditions, there is an increased risk of any grass fires
spreading rapidly.
properties.instruction:
Fasten loose objects or shelter objects in a safe location prior
to the onset of winds. Please be careful not to spark any
rangeland grass fires.

Additional graphics for this hazard can be found at
http://www.weather.gov/billings

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 11 AM THIS MORNING TO 2 AM MST SUNDAY
